chunks.html_content:
You must register and have a screening at an asylum intake unit if you’re in the UK and want to claim asylum.

You should call to make an appointment.
chunks.plain_content:
Asylum intake unit
You must register and have a screening at an asylum intake unit if you’re in the UK and want to claim asylum.
You should call to make an appointment.

chunks.html_content: You’ll have your asylum screening at the UK border if you claim asylum as soon as you arrive in the UK.
chunks.plain_content:
Asylum intake unit
You’ll have your asylum screening at the UK border if you claim asylum as soon as you arrive in the UK.

chunks.html_content: Make an appointment for screening by phoning the intake unit.

heading_context: If you have nowhere to live
chunks.html_content:
Check what you need to bring with you before you go to your appointment.

You’ll still need to call the asylum intake unit appointments line.

They’ll call you back and you may be told to attend a screening appointment or to go to a ‘walk-in’ service at an asylum registration location.

heading_context: If you have nowhere to live
chunks.html_content: If the asylum registration location does not know you’re coming you may not be seen.
chunks.plain_content:
Asylum intake unit
How to make an appointment
If you have nowhere to live
If the asylum registration location does not know you’re coming you may not be seen.

chunks.html_content:
You’ll be told where you need to go when you make an appointment.

You may be asked to come back another day if you arrive without an appointment.

You cannot get financial help for travel to or from the asylum intake unit.
chunks.plain_content:
Asylum intake unit
Where to go
You’ll be told where you need to go when you make an appointment.
You may be asked to come back another day if you arrive without an appointment.
You cannot get financial help for travel to or from the asylum intake unit.

chunks.html_content:
You’ll have to go through a security check before you’re allowed to go to your asylum screening.

You’ll be searched and you’ll go through a body scan. Your bags will also be scanned.
chunks.plain_content:
Asylum intake unit
When you arrive
You’ll have to go through a security check before you’re allowed to go to your asylum screening.
You’ll be searched and you’ll go through a body scan. Your bags will also be scanned.

chunks.html_content:
Your asylum screening can take up to 4 hours.

You may be detained after your screening. You should bring anything you need, for example medication, food and anything you need for any children you have with you.
